    <div class='simulation-container'>
      <iframe name='sim-1' class='phys-sim' src='/phys_ballistic'></iframe>
      <div class='sim-form'>
        <form method="POST">
          <div class='form__row'>
            <div class="form__fieldset">
              <label for="theta" class="form__label">Launch Angle(&Theta;):</label>
              <input type="number" step='0.01' name="theta" id="theta" class="form__input" placeholder='Angle in degrees'/>
            </div>
            <div class='form__fieldset'>
              <label for='initial_height' class='form__label'>Initial Height(H):</label>
              <input type='number' step='0.01' name='initial height' id='initial-height' class='form__input' placeholder='Height in meters'>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class='form__row'>  
            <div class="form__fieldset">
              <label for="magnatude" class="form__label">Magnatude(<span class='arrow'>U</span>):</label>
              <input type="number" step="0.01" name="magnatude" id="magnatude" class="form__input" placeholder='Launch speed(m/s)'/>
            </div>

            <div class="form__fieldset form__button_row">
              <input
                class="form__submit form__input"
                type="submit"
                value="Plot Trajectory"
              />
              <button class="form__submit form__input" id='clear-button' name="clear" value="clear">Clear</button>
            </div>
          </div>  
        </form>
        <p class='sim-description'> 
          This simulates the motion of a ball being thrown in 2d space. The simulation ignores wind resitance for the sake of simplicity.
          The greek symbol theta(&Theta;) signifies launch angle, or the angle you throw the ball with, 
          and the magnatude of the vector(<span class='arrow'>U</span>) signifies how hard you throw the ball. If you want to throw the ball
          from a non-zero height enter that into the Initial Height(H) field.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
